      "writtenOn": "2017-03-17T16:27:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "it looks like what you need here is a separate \"waiter\" class that would implement the actual waiting in a separate thread.\nYou could implement it in a separate file as a non-static class, then create an instance of this class when opening a property pipe, and use that single instance to perform waits:\n\nclass PropertyWaiter {...};\n\nclass PropertyPipe {\n    PropertyPipe(unique_ptr\u003cPropertyWaiter\u003e\u0026\u0026) { ... }\n\n    class Service {\n        PropertyPipe* create() { return new PropertyPipe(new PropertyWaiter()); }\n    };\n};\n\nThis way every class has a single function and doesn\u0027t depend on some hidden static state.\nalso, static members usually make it very difficult to understand how it works with multiple threads",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 95,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 103,
        "endChar": 46
      },
      "revId": "954fde577d739f20b49f35206efb5c1383fad250",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
